  On this day in 2015, the Supreme Court in the U.S. ruled that the country's constitution required all states to recognise same-sex marriages. The landmark 5-4 decision spurred jubilation and heartfelt reactions across the country. From exuberant rejoicing in front of the Supreme Court building to the White House lit in rainbow colours, happy couples proudly showing their marriage licences in Texas and festivities in California, memorable scenes unfolded. Here are some of the jubilant images from that day. Share this slide: Get top stories and blog posts emailed to me each day. Newsletters may offer personalized content or advertisements.
